We love good Lamb Fried Rice with Turmeric Yogurt and this deliciously simple,
chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

== Lamb Fried Rice ==

Heat a #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @lamb mince{200%g} and cook, breaking it up with a
#wooden spoon{} until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked
when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small
pieces) into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped).

Add the onion to the frying pan with the lamb and fry until softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Preheat the #grill{}.

Add the @ginger puree{1%tbsp} and @Rogan Josh curry paste{50%g} to the lamb and
stir to coat the mince.

Add the @steamed basmati rice{1%300g pack} and break it up with a #spoon{}, then
stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the coriander and cook until the rice is piping hot.

Pop the @plain naans{2} under the grill until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Turmeric Yoghurt ==

Meanwhile, pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and @ground turmeric{1/2%tsp}
in a #small bowl{} and mix well to combine. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide the rice between #bowls{}.

Drizzle the turmeric yoghurt.

Sprinkle over the @nigella seeds{1%tsp} and remaining coriander. Enjoy!